radiographic_examinations.findings: A high attenuation focus is seen in the mid appendix which may represent an appendicolith. Beyond this hyperdense focus there is relative dilation of the appendix with mild surrounding fat stranding. There is no periappendiceal fluid collection. The lung bases are clear. No pleural or pericardial effusions. The liver, spleen, gallbladder, pancreas, adrenals, kidneys and visualized portions of the ureters, stomach, visualized loops of small and large bowel are unremarkable. There is no free air or ascites. There is grade 1 retrolisthesis of L5 on S1. Visualized bony structures are otherwise unremarkable.
